<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1217">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115R39/57</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Summerlin</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 404</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 26, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s telegrams
                            Nos. 620 and 627, dated, respectively, December 8, 4 p.m., and December
                            12, 4 p.m., <pb facs="1204" n="1038" xml:id="pg_1038"/> 1917, on the
                            subject of the attack on Esperanza and the burning of the headquarters
                            of the Richardson Construction Company by Yaqui Indians, I enclose
                            herewith copies of a despatch and of its enclosure from the American
                            Consul at Guaymas, which give an account of conditions in the Yaqui
                            Valley, and of the attack, by Yaqui Indians, on Esperanza and the
                            burning of the Richardson Company’s headquarters.</p>
                        <p>You will endeavor to impress upon the Foreign Office the seriousness of
                            the situation in the Yaqui Valley as affecting American lives and
                            property.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>